  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p><p>Peel and slice the <strong>red onions</strong> into discs (approx 1/2 cm thick)</p><p>Drain the <strong>beetroot</strong> in a colander over the sink</p><p>Slice the <strong>drained beetroot </strong>into discs (approx 1/2cm thick)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion </strong>and <strong>beetroot </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until everything is beginning to brown and soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, <strong>honey </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> to a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and add 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Stir it all together until the butter has melted and everything is fully combined, then remove the pan from the heat – this is your <strong>caramel</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bash the <strong>walnuts</strong> in their bag<strong> </strong>with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until roughly crushed</p><p>Top, tail, peel and grate the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Add the <strong>crushed walnuts </strong>and <strong>grated carrot </strong>to a bowl with the <strong>rocket</strong> and gently mix together – this is your <strong>walnut salad</strong></p><p>Strip the <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them roughly, discard the stems</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onions<strong> </strong>and beetroot<strong> </strong>are done, add them to the caramel<strong> </strong>with the <strong>chopped thyme leaves</strong> and mix until evenly coated – this is your <strong>tart</strong> <strong>mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> rectangular <strong>oven-proof dish<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> with <strong>baking paper</strong> (make sure the paper pokes out the top of the dish)</p><p>Add the <strong>tart mix </strong>to the dish<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></p><p>Unroll the <strong>puff pastry</strong> and place it over the top</p><p>Crimp the edges of the<strong> pastry</strong> (slightly turn over the edges) and put the <strong>dish<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in the oven for 20 min or until the pastry is golden and crisp – this is your <strong>tarte tatin</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2467Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>tarte tatin </strong>from the oven and leave to cool for 3 min</p><p>Using the<strong> baking paper</strong>, carefully remove the <strong>tarte tatin<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> from the oven proof dish<span class=\"text-danger\">[es] </span>and transfer to a chopping board</p><p>Cut the <strong>tarte tatin<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the walnut salad<strong> </strong>and gently mix together</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
